author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Every shared dependency mutation path rejects self edges when the resolved relationship kind disallows self links, inverse and alias spellings share the rule, custom allowSelf kinds remain writable, reads render legacy self cycles truthfully, no item or history write occurs on rejection, public SDK contracts and docs explain the invariant, focused and full coverage remain 100 percent"
parent: pm-6x7o
reporter: GitHub GH-649
severity: high
resolution: "Added public assertRelationshipEdgeAllowed and shared pre-persistence dependency enforcement for create/update, with alias-aware custom allowSelf semantics and deterministic usage errors."
expected_result: Disallowed self dependencies fail before item/history writes while extension-defined allowSelf relationships remain supported.
actual_result: "CLI zero-write acceptance, public packed SDK import, real installed CLI usage=2 behavior, exact coverage, and full gates confirm the mutation boundary."
